body:
BTS, SEVENTEEN, MAMAMOO, BLACKPINK, And More Take Spots On Billboard’s World Albums Chart

Billboard has released its charts for the week ending in June 28, with many Korean artists taking spots on the World Albums chart!

BTS’s “Love Yourself: Tear” remains at No. 1 on the World Albums chart, now in its ninth week overall on the chart. “Love Yourself: Her” is also still at No. 2, remaining on the chart for its 44th week.
